<HEADLINE>
<P>
THEME FOOD; 
</P>
<P>
IF YOU WANT TO HAVE A GOOD TIME, BRING ALONG A SENSE OF HUMOR. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
California Beach, 7656 Melrose Ave., Los Angeles. (213) 655-0123. Style: 
Familiar Japanese dishes served at ear-splitting noise levels. Setting: Surf 
city with performing sushi chefs. 
</P>
<P>
Beach room available for private parties. Recommended: Fried dumplings; 
cucumber-octopus salad; deep-fried green tea ice cream. Cost per person: 
$12-$28. 
</P>
<P>
El Mocambo, 8338 West 3rd St., Los Angeles. (213) 651-2113. Style: Ricky 
Ricardo's kind of Cuba. Setting: Tutti-frutti. Waiters waltz around in tight 
uniforms serving drinks with names like "Bay of Pigs" and "Babaloo-Loo Loo." 
Recommended: Corn chowder; tostones; Americano Loco steak. Cost per person: 
$15-$30. 
</P>
<P>
La Cave, 7070 Hollywood Blvd., Hollywood. (213) 460-7070. Style: Five set menus 
(French, Aphrodisiac, Exotic, Spa and Italian) inside a rock nightclub. 
Setting: Cavelike. Recommended: The Exotic dinner (green salad laced with duck 
meat; shrimp curry with fresh pineapple and passion-fruit ice). Cost per 
person: $18-$28. 
</P>
<P>
Mickey's Kitchen, 5060 Montclair Plaza Lane, Space 5010, Montclair. (714) 
624-8111. Style: Disney-owned restaurant inside a Disney-owned store, for kids 
of all ages. Setting: Many reminders of Mickey and his friends. Recommended: 
Goofy burger; piglet corkscrew fries; supercalifragi-chicken salad. Cost per 
person: $5-$8. 
</P>
<P>
Stitches, 1927 1/2 Zonal Ave., Lincoln Heights. (213) 222-0221. Style: 
Sophisticated lunch counter with the right palate prescription. Setting: Across 
from USC Medical Center's Emergency Admitting -- waiters wear green operating 
theater tunics; beverages are dispensed from I.V. units. Recommended: Grilled 
chicken breast with garlic slivers; chicken Alfredo; barbecued chicken pizza. 
Cost per person: $7-$15. Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</TEXT>
