<HEADLINE>
<P>
REPLYING FOR THE DEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
R.A. Lee's July 29 letter regarding stars supposedly "outed" (alleged to be 
homosexual) since their deaths merits response, since they cannot reply. 
</P>
<P>
Buster Wiles, Errol Flynn's stunt double and close friend for 24 years, scoffed 
at claims Flynn was attracted to men. 
</P>
<P>
In 1980, Cary Grant sued Chevy Chase for commenting "I understand he is a 
homo." In a deposition, Chase admitted he didn't know what he was talking 
about. 
</P>
<P>
The later holds true for tabloid biographers, eager to feast unfairly on the 
dead, for money. 
</P>
<P>
WILLIAM DONATI 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
<P>
 "My Days With Errol Flynn" by Buster Wiles with William Donati, was published 
in 1988. 
