<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fred Bowen, resident manager of the NASA office at the Jet Propulsion 
Laboratory, has been elected chairman of United Way's San Gabriel Valley 
regional board of directors. 
</P>
<P>
He will preside over the all-volunteer board, which establishes policy for 
raising money. The board in past years has distributed more than $8 million a 
year to local health and human service agencies. United Way's San Gabriel 
region extends from Pasadena and Monterey Park on the west to Glendora and 
Rowland Heights on the east. 
</P>
