<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Raymond Girvigian, a South Pasadena historical preservation architect, has been 
honored by two cultural groups for his career achievements in the preservation 
of historical landmarks. 
</P>
<P>
He received a Gold Crown Award from the Pasadena Arts Council and the Golden 
Palm Award from Hollywood Heritage. 
</P>
<P>
Girvigian is known for his restoration and consulting work on numerous 
projects, including the state Capitol, the Pasadena and Los Angeles central 
libraries, the Riverside Mission Inn and the Workman Temple Homestead Museum in 
Industry. He serves on the State Historical Building Code Board and is chairman 
of the State Historic Capitol Commission. 
</P>
