<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
William and Ethel Tibbetts of El Monte have been honored by President Bush for 
their volunteer work on behalf of the disabled. 
</P>
<P>
The couple were named as Bush's 208th "Daily Point of Light" in a program to 
honor exemplary public service or volunteer work. The designation has been 
issued six days a week since November. 
</P>
<P>
The Tibbettses have volunteered for the Disabled American Veterans 
Transportation Network since 1986. They spend nine hours a day assisting 
disabled veterans by providing transportation, visiting them in their homes and 
phoning them to be sure they receive the help they need. 
</P>
