<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRM RECEIVES HONORS FOR NO-SMOKING POLICY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Santa Monica-based National Medical Enterprises Inc. is the first company to be 
recognized by the American Lung Assn. of los Angeles County for having a 
smoke-free workplace. 
</P>
<P>
The company has declared that it will not allow smoking at its new corporate 
offices at 2700 Colorado Ave in addition more than half of the firm's 37 
acute-care hospitals throughout the country are smoke-free or plan to convert 
to no-smoking environments. 
</P>
<P>
The lung association this year plans to acknowledge 100 companies in the county 
that establish smoke-free policies. 
</P>
