<HEADLINE>
<P>
A ROCKY MOUNTAIN HIGH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Polly C. Rogers 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Getting there: Estes Park is 65 miles northwest of Denver, a scenic 1 1/2-hour 
drive. Take Interstate 25 north from Denver to Highway 36 (Boulder Turnpike), 
through Boulder and Lyons into Estes Park. 
</P>
<P>
Where to stay: Accommodations in Estes Park range from the plush and historic 
Stanley Hotel to rustic log cabins and campgrounds that are open year-round. 
Last-minute accommodations could be difficult to find. Rates at the Stanley 
range from $60 to $120 per night. Write Stanley Hotel, P.O. Box 1767, Estes 
Park, Colo. 80517, or call (303) 586-3371. 
</P>
<P>
When to go: The next Scottish-Irish Festival will be held Saturday and Sunday, 
Sept. 8-9, at the Stanley Park Field, Highway 36 and Community Drive in Estes 
Park. Hours are 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. each day. Gate passes are $9 for adults, $2 
for children 6-16, younger children free. Special two-day adult pass is $14. 
Tickets for the Tattoo are $10 apiece. 
</P>
<P>
For more information: Contact the Estes Park Chamber of Commerce, 500 Big 
Thompson Ave., P.O. Box 3050, Estes Park, Colo. 80517, (800) 443-7837. Polly C. 
Rogers 
</P>
</TEXT>
