<HEADLINE>
<P>
L.A. VS. ORANGE COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There was nothing in "L.A. vs O.C.: A Special Report" (June 17) that a 
10-minute drive through either county would not reveal. 
</P>
<P>
Generally, the article was a presentation of data of well-known facts. That is, 
Orange County: Republican, white, "parties," wealth, condos, surfers. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles County: Polluted, crime, urbane, culture sites, freeways, racial 
diversity. 
</P>
<P>
What I said in two sentences took Patt Morrison ("Family Feud") 12 pages. What 
a waste. 
</P>
<P>
HAATSARI KAGURABADZA 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
