<HEADLINE>
<P>
L.A. VS. ORANGE COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"One in six . . . commute to earn an L.A. paycheck and enjoy it in Orange 
County" is a strong argument for an L.A. income tax -- on O.C. and other 
commuters. This is in fact a practice in some eastern cities. 
</P>
<P>
Capital is generated by L.A., drained into O.C. by commuter spending and tax 
flight, leaving L.A. with a permanent tax imbalance. Amenities not affordable 
by L.A. communities are enjoyed in O.C., paid by taxes whose source is L.A. 
</P>
<P>
DON MANNING 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
