<HEADLINE>
<P>
BAUBLES, BANGLES AND BRAIDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA THACKABERRY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Long hair is still in style, and it's anything but boring -- innovative hair 
ornaments made of everything from silk to marble are becoming a must. Gone are 
high-maintenance, moussed hairdos -- replaced with clasped, knotted or pinned 
sculptural ponytails, braids and chignons. 
</P>
<P>
Astute jewelry and beauty-industry designers are creating ornaments rich in 
color and baroque in shape to match current fashion trends. Materials include 
fabric, wood, metals, wire, acrylics and gold leaf. Bejeweled or sculpted hair 
sticks secure a bun or French twist, while the common hair bow adopts the more 
sophisticated look of stainless steel mesh. And don't settle for a plain old 
rubber band to hold hair in place -- go for a wired silk rope or spiral of 
copper, which lends elegance to even a simple ponytail. LISA THACKABERRY 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
