CEREMONIES UNDER WAY FOR AKIHITO'S CORONATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Members of the imperial court have buried rice, salt, linen and silk in a 
ground-breaking ceremony preparing a site for Emperor Akihito's coronation next 
fall. 
</P>
<P>
Akihito, 56, became emperor in January, 1989, upon the death of his father, 
Emperor Hirohito. The coronation was delayed by a yearlong mourning period. 
</P>
