<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: OCEANSIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 19-year-old woman who Oceanside police thought had been abducted by her 
boyfriend has turned up in Tijuana because the two eloped, a police spokesman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
"They were going to get married and go to Mexico City," said spokesman Sgt. 
Bill Krunglevich. 
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, witnesses told police that they saw Irma Martinez being forced into 
a van in the 1600 block of Kraft Street by two men, one of whom was identified 
as her ex-boyfriend, George Rios, 20, of Oceanside. 
</P>
<P>
After sending investigators to Tijuana Wednesday night, Oceanside police closed 
the case after determining that Martinez was with Rios because she wanted to 
be. 
</P>
</TEXT>
