<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: COUNTYWIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego Sheriff's deputies are investigating an apparent murder-suicide in 
Cameron Corners near Campo on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
An unidentified citizen flagged down Sheriff Patrol Deputy William C. Smith at 
about 5 p.m. after the residents of the home located in the 1700 block of 
Buckman Springs failed to keep a morning appointment, said Lt. John Tenwold. 
</P>
<P>
On entering the home, Smith discovered the body of a white man who appeared to 
be in his 60s and a white woman in her 50s. 
</P>
<P>
The couple were not identified pending notification of relatives. Sheriff's 
deputies are continuing their investigation. 
</P>
