<HEADLINE>
<P>
100 FLEE BLAST SITE AFTER PROPANE LEAK FOUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CINCINNATI 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 100 workers cleaning up a plant rocked by fatal explosions last month 
were evacuated Saturday after a propane leak was discovered. 
</P>
<P>
Cincinnati police said the leak came from a large tank buried in the rubble of 
the BASF Corp. plant, but it was quickly contained. No one was injured. 
</P>
<P>
A series of blasts at the plant on July 19 killed one worker and injured at 
least 68 other people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
