<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHITTIER COLLEGE LIBRARY PICKED FOR ROLE IN U.S. INFORMATION TEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WHITTIER 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Whittier College's Wardman Library has been selected as one of 100 U.S. test 
sites to participate in the 1990 Economic Bulletin Board pilot project. 
</P>
<P>
The program, sponsored by the Government Printing Office, the Commerce 
Department and the General Accounting Office, was established in 1985 to 
provide on-line access to numerical and textual data published by the Commerce 
Department and other sources, including the Census Bureau, the Bureau of Labor 
Statistics, the Federal Reserve Board and the U.S. Treasury Department. 
</P>
<P>
The aim is to study public response to the provision of direct computerized 
access to government information. More than 400 files are available, including 
economic and employment statistics, the consumer price index, the gross 
national product and Daily Trade Opportunities for Exporters. 
</P>
<P>
Information may be viewed on screen, printed out or downloaded to a disk. The 
database is available for public use weekdays at the library from 8 a.m to noon 
and from 1 p.m. to 4:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
For information, contact the Wardman Library, Whittier College, 13406 
Philadelphia St., Whittier, or call 693-0771. 
</P>
</TEXT>
