<HEADLINE>
<P>
HAMBLETONIAN TO HARMONIOUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Harmonious took the lead midway through the stretch and then held off Embassy 
Lobell by 1 1/2 lengths Saturday to win the $1,346,000 Hambletonian at the 
Meadowlands in straight heats. 
</P>
<P>
The Hambletonian victory was the third in four years for driver John Campbell 
and it also gave owner Frank Antonacci and his Lindy Racing Stable a record 
fourth victory. 
</P>
<P>
Harmonious and Embassy Lobell were both impressive in winning their divisions 
of the opening heat. Harmonious was by far the better horse in the second heat, 
trotting the mile 1:54 1/5, the third fastest heat in the 65-year history of 
the Hambletonian, the foremost trotting event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
