<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. TOP SEEDED AT SYNCHRONIZED SWIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Despite finishing third in the compulsory team figures competition Saturday, 
the United States will be the top-seeded team in today's finals of the American 
Cup IV synchronized swimming competition at Heritage Park in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
The U.S. team earned the No. 1 seeding because it had the top combined score 
(166.8800) from the preliminaries. 
</P>
<P>
China (166.6550) is second, followed by Canada (166.5588), Egypt (150.6850), 
Switzerland (148.6788), France (137.4150), West Germany (135.7360) and Mexico 
(131.6550). 
</P>
<P>
In the preliminary team routines, the United States finished first with a score 
of 96.30. Canada (92.40) was second and China (91.48) third. 
</P>
<P>
In an upset, China won the team compulsory figures with a score of 75.1750. 
Favorites Canada (74.1588) and the United States (73.2800) finished second and 
third. 
</P>
<P>
Today's finals start at 2 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
