<HEADLINE>
<P>
RERUNS TO REWATCH: THE GOAT THAT ALMOST ATE MAYBERRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOAN FANTAZIA, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sleepy Mayberry wakes up for a while when an ornery billy goat swallows some 
dynamite in "The Loaded Goat" on The Andy Griffith Show (Friday at 3:35 p.m. on 
TBS). 
</P>
<P>
Usually the town's biggest danger is Barney Fife, but this time Jimmy the goat 
even has Barney beat. 
</P>
<P>
Jimmy, who had insisted on coming to town to see the sights, gets loose and 
snacks on some explosives meant for highway work. ("First time he comes uptown 
he figures he's got to do everything," complains Jimmy's owner, Cy Hudgins). 
</P>
<P>
Barney and Andy put Jimmy in a sort of padded cell to keep him safe, but the 
goat's run-in with a drunken Otis- who doesn't like his new roommate- threatens 
to blow their plans sky-high. (Warns Andy: "About one loaded goat at a time is 
all we can handle.") 
</P>
<P>
In the end, thanks to Andy's brains and Barney's French harp playing, the goat 
winds up in one piece- and so does Mayberry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Jimmy the Goat has Sheriff Andy Taylor (Andy Griffith) and Deputy Barney 
Fife (Don Knotts) a little concerned for the town's safety because of dynamite 
the goat ate for a snack. "The Loaded Goat" episode of "The Andy Griffith Show" 
airs Friday at 3:35 p.m. on TBS. VIACOM ENTERPRISES 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
